replies.body:
In general Mages get outclassed by their lack of scaling with primary stats.
If you look at AD champions who scale extremely well with, AS, Crit, AD, Lifesteal, CDR (5 total). 
Compared to AP champions who scale extremely well with, AP, CDR... Yeah that's it... and as it stands AD have better CDR options

Then on top of that AP have their mana much more emphasized than AD champions, despite AD champions being just as ability dependent in many cases.

They might have "healthier" items, but the healthy ones almost always weaker? 
{{item:3151}} < {{item:3153}} 
{{item:3165}} < {{item:3033}} 
{{item:3191}} < {{item:3155}} 

Mages seem to run into these problems more than AP assassins, if not only because mobility can be substituted for power in many cases.

What mages need are either AP utility scaling (because we all know how much people love those on lulu), or more multiplier stats. Bring Spell vamp back (nerf vlad to compensate w/e), give them items which increase their max CDR, so AD can get 40% let mages get 60%.
